  "prompt": "Are Territorial army officers getting permanent commission now a days?",
  "response": "The policies regarding permanent commissions for Territorial Army officers can change based on the needs of the military and government decisions. As of my last update, Territorial Army officers typically serve on a part-time basis and are not usually granted permanent commissions in the same way as officers in the regular army. However, there have been instances where exceptional Territorial Army officers have been considered for permanent commissions or have been absorbed into the regular army based on specific needs and policies in place at the time.\n\nFor the most current and accurate information, it would be best to consult the official website of the Indian Army or contact the Territorial Army directly. They can provide the latest updates on policies regarding permanent commissions for Territorial Army officers.",
